Tested 30+ properties on html module - all passed ✅

The `html.escape()` and `html.unescape()` functions correctly implement HTML5 entity handling, including:
- Round-trip property for valid strings
- Proper handling of invalid Unicode codepoints
- HTML5 partial entity matching rules
- Numeric entities with/without semicolons
- Special character replacements
- Edge cases with very large numbers and malformed entities
